SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: MAINSTREET ORGANIZATION OF REALTORS IS A NOT-FOR-PROFIT ORGANIZATION THAT IS EXEMPT FROM INCOME TAXES UNDER SECTION 501(C)(6) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE (IRC). THE ORGANIZATION IS NOT CLASSIFIED AS A PRIVATE FOUNDATION. THE DUPAGE ASSOCIATION OF REALTORS MULTIPLE LISTING SERVICE, INC. OPERATES AS A FOR-PROFIT CORPORATION AND IS LIABLE FOR FEDERAL AND STATE INCOME TAXES. THE ORGANIZATION FOLLOWS AUTHORITATIVE GUIDANCE ISSUED BY THE FINANCIAL ACCOUNTING STANDARDS BOARD (FASB) THAT CLARIFIES THE ACCOUNTING FOR UNCERTAINTY IN INCOME TAXES RECOGNIZED IN AN ENTITY'S FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND PRESCRIBES A RECOGNITION THRESHOLD OF MORE-LIKELY-THAN-NOT TO BE SUSTAINED UPON EXAMINATION. MEASUREMENT OF THE TAX UNCERTAINTY OCCURS IF THE RECOGNITION THRESHOLD HAS NOT BEEN MET. THIS GUIDANCE ALSO ADDRESSES DERECOGNITION, CLASSIFICATION, INTEREST AND PENALTIES, DISCLOSURE, AND TRANSITION. THE ORGANIZATION CONDUCTS BUSINESS SOLELY IN THE U.S. AND, AS A RESULT, FILES INFORMATION RETURNS FOR U.S. AND ILLINOIS. IN THE NORMAL COURSE OF BUSINESS, THE ORGANIZATION IS SUBJECT TO EXAMINATION BY TAXING AUTHORITIES. PAC IS A SEPARATE SEGREGATED FUND OF THE ORGANIZATION. PAC IS ONLY SUBJECT TO INCOME TAX AS A SEPARATE SEGREGATED FUND UNDER SECTION 527 OF THE IRC ON INVESTMENT INCOME, IF ANY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION HAS 8 CLASSES OF MEMBERS WHICH INCLUDES: REALTOR MEMBERS, AFFILIATE MEMBERS, PUBLIC SERVICE MEMBERS, HONORARY MEMBERS, STUDENT MEMBERS, REALTORS EMERITUS MEMBERS, HONORARY LIFE MEMBERS AND DISTIGNUISHED MEMBERS. REALTOR MEMBERS ARE GIVEN VOTING RIGHTS. ALL OF THE MEMBERS PRIVILEGES AND OBLIGATIONS ARE OUTLINED IN THE ORGANIZATION'S BY-LAWS AND AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ALL REALTOR MEMBERS OF THE ORGANIZATION ARE GIVEN THE OPTION TO VOTE TO ELECT THE MEMBERS OF THE BOARD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS SHALL PASS A RESOLUTION AUTHORIZING THE SUBMISSION OF THE QUESTION OR QUESTIONS TO BE VOTED UPON BY THE MEMBERSHIP. VOTING PROCEDURES ARE OUTLINED IN THE ORGANIZATION'S BY-LAWS AND ARE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: A FORMAL REVIEW OF THE 990 IS CONDUCTED BY THE AUDIT COMMITTEE PRIOR TO FILING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: REVIEW OF CONFLICTS, IF ANY, ARE CONSIDERED AT MONTHLY BOARD MEETINGS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: EMPLOYEE COMPENSATION IS COMPARED TO MARKET STUDIES FOR SIMILAR ORGANIZATIONS FOR REASONABLENESS. COMPENSATION FOR THE CEO IS REVIEWED AND APPROVED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. COMPENSATION FOR OTHER POSITIONS IS REVIEWED AND APPROVED BY THE CEO.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: DOCUMENTS ARE MADE AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
